From: labelle-toolkit
Date: 2026-05-18
Subject: [PATCH] sokol-zig: expose SOKOL_IMGUI_NO_SOKOL_APP via build option

sokol_imgui.h already supports a SOKOL_IMGUI_NO_SOKOL_APP compile-time
flag that disables its sokol_app dependency. The caller passes
width/height/dpi_scale/delta_time explicitly to simgui_new_frame, and
the keyboard/mouse-cursor helpers that read from sokol_app become
no-ops. This is exactly what a headless render-to-texture workflow
needs (e.g. an editor preview that renders into a shared IOSurface
without owning an NSWindow).

sokol-zig's build.zig exposes `with_sokol_imgui` for the bindings but
doesn't currently forward `SOKOL_IMGUI_NO_SOKOL_APP`. This patch adds
a parallel `with_sokol_imgui_no_app` option that defines the flag when
compiling sokol_imgui.c. Default is `false` — fully backward
compatible; existing users see no change.

Tested locally as part of labelle-assembler#140 (labelle-toolkit's
no-window editor-preview work).

--- a/build.zig
+++ b/build.zig
@@ -73,1 +73,2 @@
     const opt_with_sokol_imgui = b.option(bool, "with_sokol_imgui", "Add support for sokol_imgui.h bindings") orelse false;
+    const opt_with_sokol_imgui_no_app = b.option(bool, "with_sokol_imgui_no_app", "Define SOKOL_IMGUI_NO_SOKOL_APP when compiling sokol_imgui.h (headless mode — no sokol_app dependency)") orelse false;
     const opt_with_tracing = b.option(bool, "with_tracing", "Add support for sokol_gfx tracing and debug UI") orelse false;
@@ -95,1 +96,2 @@
         .with_sokol_imgui = opt_with_sokol_imgui or opt_with_tracing,
+        .with_sokol_imgui_no_app = opt_with_sokol_imgui_no_app,
         .with_tracing = opt_with_tracing,
@@ -141,1 +143,8 @@
     with_sokol_imgui: bool = false,
+    /// Define SOKOL_IMGUI_NO_SOKOL_APP — disables sokol_app dependency in
+    /// sokol_imgui.h. The caller must pass `width`/`height`/`dpi_scale`
+    /// explicitly to `simgui_new_frame`; keyboard/mouse cursor helpers
+    /// that read from sokol_app become no-ops. Useful for headless
+    /// preview / render-to-texture setups.
+    with_sokol_imgui_no_app: bool = false,
     with_tracing: bool = false,
@@ -316,1 +325,4 @@
     if (options.with_sokol_imgui) {
+        if (options.with_sokol_imgui_no_app) {
+            try cflags.appendBounded("-DSOKOL_IMGUI_NO_SOKOL_APP");
+        }
         if (options.sokol_imgui_cprefix) |cprefix| {

Usage from a consuming build.zig:

    const dep_sokol = b.dependency("sokol", .{
        .target = target,
        .optimize = optimize,
        .with_sokol_imgui = true,
        .with_sokol_imgui_no_app = true,
    });

Consumers must then provide width/height to simgui_new_frame manually
instead of relying on sapp_*. See labelle-toolkit/labelle-imgui's
bridges/sokol/src/bridge.zig for a reference pattern that falls back
to sane defaults when sapp returns zeros.

Upstream:
    https://github.com/floooh/sokol-zig
This patch is local-only until upstreamed; while pending it must be
applied to the cached sokol-zig copy at
    ~/.cache/zig/p/sokol-0.1.0-<hash>/build.zig

after any fresh `zig fetch`.
